race.comment: The lightly raced INSTA WORTHY (1) is back from a 23-week spell. Opened last prep well enough then failed at Ipswich and was turned out. Now a gelding and the Dunn stable pop the blinkers on. Easy recent trial winner who looks set to realise his potential this time in work. BEEARETEE (5) had a change of tactics and went to the front last start over this trip at Grafton and was only overhauled close to the line. Gets a few significant gear changes and at just the third run of the prep could prove hard to beat. MISS MIDAS TOUCH (2) was poorly away but rallied late to be beaten just over a length when resuming at Grafton recently. Might switch on a little better today with the blinkers applied. Right in contention. COPENHAGEN CAT (6) was brave in defeat after leading at Grafton last time. Has had plenty of chances but worth some thought based on that latest effort. HIGHWIRE GIRL (7) did a good job at massive odds on debut last start - cannot be underestimated.
